Maybe for cases like this where the list is only consumed once it would make sense to add a mapLazy that is based on something like this:
static class LazyMapList<I, O> extends AbstractList<O> {

    private final List<I> list;
    private final Function<? super I, ? extends O> mapper;

    public LazyMapList(List<I> list, Function<? super I, ? extends O> mapper) {
        this.list = list;
        this.mapper = mapper;
    }

    @Override
    public O get(int index) {
        return mapper.apply(list.get(index));
    }

    @Override
    public int size() {
        return list.size();
    }
}

